First factor out the perfect‐square part from each radical:

\[
\sqrt{72a^5}
=\sqrt{72\cdot a^4\cdot a}
=\sqrt{36\cdot2\cdot a^4\cdot a}
=6\,a^2\sqrt{2a},
\]

\[
\sqrt{50a^5}
=\sqrt{50\cdot a^4\cdot a}
=\sqrt{25\cdot2\cdot a^4\cdot a}
=5\,a^2\sqrt{2a}.
\]

Hence

\[
\sqrt{72a^5}-\sqrt{50a^5}
=6a^2\sqrt{2a}-5a^2\sqrt{2a}
=(6-5)a^2\sqrt{2a}
=a^2\sqrt{2a}.
\]
